::Firaxis/Horn::
       He nods and smiles inwardly at himself.  His obedience had startled 
her, this was a good sign.  He stands at attention and slams his right hand 
against the left side of his chest, this serves the double purpose of a 
solute and implanting the chip for reading.  With that he spins on his heel 
and heads toward the coordinates.

       He leans over and whispers to Horn. "Begin work on that surveillance 
device.  I want to transmit to her any signs of intelligent life that comes 
within two miles of these coordinates."

--part1_62.20c56f64.2a32c529_boundary
